<br>
That being said, I really don't feel comfortable setting up a camp to provide every paladin within a few blocks with something that they can obtain passively through us.  I experienced this the other day when I was helping kill spawn for a part of Allerielle's mage epic.  It took alot of time for Allerielle to coordinate and find people to help her complete that task.  Once she was finally able to acquire the necessary persons to achieve the task, we set forth to accomplish it.  We ultimately ended up providing the epic piece for 2 other mages during the course of the camp.  I felt bad because I had just taken something that was a difficult task for Allerielle to complete, and made it easy for 2 mages that I have never met.  And although extremely grateful, those mages didn't get to experience what the true meaning of an epic is about sometimes--the frustration and difficulty of coordinating groups to achieve a purely self-centered task.<br>
<br>
I have no problems trying to get hilts for Valmar &amp; Gokulot.  I have known them, and faught along side with them.  I consider them worthy of the Soulfire.  But my paladin instincts tell me that I can't afford to provide something to others that I'm not totally positive are worthy of.  I will help aid Valmar &amp; Gokulot.  But I can't for the life of me aid those on an epic quest that I have no indications of being worthy of such an item.<br>
<br>
